
AgentGov: Enterprise AI Governance & Delegation
Tagline: Enterprise AI Governance: Turn Autonomous Agents into Accountable Assets.
Executive Summary
AgentGov is an enterprise governance platform that enables organizations to deploy AI agents with verifiable identity, delegated authority, and cryptographically auditable actions. As enterprises integrate AI agents into procurement, legal, and financial operations, the critical challenge is verification—ensuring agents are authorized, compliant, and acting within defined boundaries. AgentGov solves this using the Terminal 3 Agent Auth SDK, providing a trusted framework where agents act on behalf of users while remaining fully accountable.
The Problem
Enterprises are rapidly deploying AI, but face systemic governance limitations:
•	Lack of Verifiable Identity: No standard to prove an agent’s authority.
•	Governance Gap: No framework to delegate authority or set operational limits.
•	Auditability Failure: No cryptographic proof of decision-making.
•	Policy Blindness: Agents lack "policy-aware" execution controls.
The Solution
AgentGov creates a trust layer for autonomous workflows. By utilizing Terminal 3’s hardware-secured Trusted Execution Environments (TEEs), AgentGov ensures that all identity and policy evaluations occur in an isolated, tamper-proof environment.
•	Verifiable Identity: Agents authenticate securely before accessing systems.
•	Delegated Authority: Define explicit approval limits and operational boundaries.
•	Policy Enforcement: Automated compliance checks against organizational rules before action execution.
•	Auditable Decisions: Every action produces a traceable, cryptographic record.



AgentGov Architecture Flow
Human Identity
↓
Delegated Authority
↓
Terminal 3 Agent Auth (TEE)
↓
Verified Agent Identity
↓
Policy Engine
↓
Authorized Action
↓
Cryptographic Audit Trail

Example Use Cases
•	Legal Firms: Contract Review Agents analyze agreements but escalate to partners for final execution.
•	Procurement: Vendor Management Agents review supplier credentials against internal risk policies.
•	Financial Services: Compliance Agents perform automated KYC/AML checks with full audit logging.
Why Terminal 3
Built on Terminal 3’s Agent Auth SDK, AgentGov leverages:
•	Hardware-Secured Security: TEE-powered infrastructure for privacy-preserving operations.
•	Trust Foundation: Secure agent-to-system authentication without central points of failure.
•	Cryptographic Proof: Verifiable evidence for every delegated action.
Business Impact
•	Accelerated Adoption: Deploy agents with confidence.
•	Risk Mitigation: Reduce governance and compliance overhead.
•	Regulatory Readiness: Maintain enterprise-grade accountability for all autonomous workflows.
Vision
The future of enterprise AI will not be determined by how intelligent agents become, but by how trustworthy they are.
AgentGov provides the governance infrastructure that allows organizations to deploy AI agents at scale while preserving security, accountability, and trust.
Trust Every Agent. Verify Every Action.


